    "created_at": "2012-12-08T14:32:57Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-12-08T14:32:57Z",
    "body": "I don't think it's really fixed.  If you modify the test case to include a \"move\" capture clause, it still reproduces:\n\n```\nstruct NoCopy {\n    n: int\n}\nfn NoCopy() -> NoCopy {\n    NoCopy { n: 0 }\n}\n\nimpl NoCopy: Drop {\n    fn finalize(&self) {\n        log(error, \"running destructor\");\n    }\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    let x = NoCopy();\n\n    let f = fn~(move x) { assert x.n == 0; }; \n    let g = copy f; // <-- Error expected here\n\n    f(); g();\n}\n```\n\nThe proper fix is the work on closure bounds I did not get to for 0.5!\n",
